history.content:
My understanding in seven years on campus is that waitlists can't be "cut" or "dropped", but that the number doesn't really indicate much given that courses enroll based on seats in the discussion/lab sections, and may use enrollment groups to give priority to different students. 


That being said, there have obviously been some issues with the new system, including some students being randomly dropped from the waitlist. My only guess is that one of these students was re-added to their original seat, ahead of you. Again, that could be totally wrong. 


I would encourage you to contact the SIS team to notify them of this issue.

I was waitlist position 41 in CS 189 yesterday, and I am now position 42. Is it possible to fall to a lower position on the waitlist, and if so, how can I avoid this? I thought waitlists were queues, and that there is no cutting or dropping to lower positions once in them?
